{{Refimprove|date=July 2018}}
A '''cell culture assay''' is any method which is used to assess the [[cytotoxicity]] of a material.<ref>{{cite journal|title=A cell culture assay for the detection of cardiotoxicity|journal=Journal of pharmacological methods|volume=25|issue=2|pages=133–45|pmid=1712416|year=1991|author1=Löw-Friedrich|first1=I|last2=von Bredow|first2=F|last3=Schoeppe|first3=W}}</ref>  This refers to the ''[[in vitro]]'' assessment of a material to determine whether it releases toxic chemicals in sufficient quantities to kill cells either directly or indirectly through the inhibition of cell metabolic pathways.  Cell culture evaluations are the precursor to whole animal studies and are a way to determine if significant cytotoxicity exists for the given material.  Cell culture assays are standardized by [[ASTM]], [[International Organization for Standardization|ISO]], and BSI ([[British Standards Institution]].)

